Well what we could do is we could go to Sec.gov

128
00:08:02,045 --> 00:08:06,505
that's the Securities and Exchange Commission.gov

129
00:08:06,505 --> 00:08:08,126
that's a government website of course

130
00:08:08,126 --> 00:08:11,664
and find the annual reports for companies like Google

131
00:08:11,664 --> 00:08:15,831
and then we can quote these annual reports just like this.

132
00:08:21,149 --> 00:08:23,746
Now let's say you're giving a presentation

133
00:08:23,746 --> 00:08:25,978
and you want to put data in your presentation

134
00:08:25,978 --> 00:08:28,453
on the topic of Human Resources.

135
00:08:28,453 --> 00:08:32,702
You have no idea what to present and you just need ideas.

136
00:08:32,702 --> 00:08:36,317
Go to Google and see what the auto response is

137
00:08:36,317 --> 00:08:39,038
for "what is human resources"

138
00:08:39,038 --> 00:08:41,780
"why does human resources etc."

139
00:08:41,780 --> 00:08:43,947
Just check this out.

140
00:08:43,947 --> 00:08:46,579
When you start typing something, a drop box appears

141
00:08:46,579 --> 00:08:48,916
and you can kind of find out

142
00:08:48,916 --> 00:08:50,691
what the most popular searches are

143
00:08:50,691 --> 00:08:53,413
and it might spark an idea for you.

144
00:08:53,413 --> 00:08:54,924
Here's another one for you.

145
00:08:54,924 --> 00:08:59,460
Go to Quora.com, that's Q-U-O-R-A.com

146
00:08:59,460 --> 00:09:02,528
and search on your presentation topic

147
00:09:02,528 --> 00:09:04,861
for data or reference ideas.

148
